## Phase 1..N: Team Engagements ‚Äî Sequential, Full Depth

Phases execute in the PROCESS.md order ‚Äî strict, never parallel (each consumes the
prior's artifacts):

| # | Bootstrap phase | Skill file to load | Modes |
|---|-----------------|--------------------|-------|
| 1 | Strategy | `enterprise-strategy/SKILL.md` | `--landscape` ‚Üí `--market` ‚Üí `--pricing` ‚Üí `--growth` |
| 2 | Positioning + ICP | `enterprise-marketing/SKILL.md`, then `enterprise-sales/SKILL.md` | `--positioning`; `--icp` |
| 3 | Finance | `enterprise-finance/SKILL.md` | `--model` ‚Üí `--runway` (+ `--pricing-study` if Phase 1 produced a WTP study spec) |
| 4 | Legal & compliance | `enterprise-compliance/SKILL.md`, then `enterprise-legal/SKILL.md` | `--applicability`; `--paper` (stage-gated) |
| 5 | Activation | marketing / sales / customer-success / people / bizops / deployment skill files | per the stage-calibration table (`/deployment --design` when anything ships to production and no plan of record exists; `--audit` when a pipeline already exists) |
| 6 | Board pass | `enterprise-review/SKILL.md` | target: `docs/enterprise/` |

Skill files live at `~/.claude/skills/gstack/enterprise-<team>/SKILL.md` (fallback:
`enterprise-<team>/SKILL.md` relative to the gstack repo; the customer-success team's
directory is `enterprise-success/`). Read the ENTIRE file, and Read each playbook the
executed mode references.

**Section skip list ‚Äî when following a loaded team skill, SKIP:**
- Preamble (run first) ‚Äî already ran
- Phase 0 foundation interviews ‚Äî replaced by the Fact Intake (team foundations are
  still WRITTEN, from intake facts, in each team's Phase 0 format, activation line
  included)
- Phase 1 mode selection ‚Äî modes are predetermined above
- AskUserQuestion Format / completeness / telemetry boilerplate
- The Phase 6 "recommend the process doc / suggest next skill" handoff prose ‚Äî
  /enterprise-autoplan owns sequencing

Everything else runs in full: evidence gathering, persona passes, playbook-structured
artifacts, quality-gate tables, Phase 6 persistence (dated files, headers, review-gate
footers, INDEX.md, and the human to-do items written to their own dated action-checklist file
per the Action Checklist convention ‚Äî never left only inline).

**Consultant reviews are mandatory.** Each team's Phase 4 runs as a real foreground
Agent subagent (`subagent_type: "general-purpose"`, never `run_in_background`) with the
prompt the skill specifies. Findings: mechanical ‚Üí fix and log; Taste ‚Üí adopt the
recommendation, log, queue for the gate; User Challenge ‚Üí queue for the gate untouched
(ship the artifact with the user's direction plus a `<!-- USER CHALLENGE pending -->`
marker).

**Between phases**, emit a transition summary ‚Äî artifacts written, consultant verdict,
decisions logged (M mechanical / T taste / U challenges) ‚Äî and verify the prior phase's
files exist on disk before starting the next. If a phase's quality gates land on
`NEEDS WORK`, fix and re-gate (max 2 attempts), then proceed with the gap named in the
gate table and at the final gate.

