## Final Approval Gate

**STOP and present.** Then AskUserQuestion.

```
## /enterprise-autoplan Complete

### The plan
[2-4 sentences: what now exists in docs/enterprise/, stage tier applied, teams run]

### Board verdict: [READY / NEEDS WORK] ‚Äî board score [N]/10

### User Challenges ([U]) ‚Äî your direction stands unless you change it
[each: you said ¬∑ the review recommends ¬∑ why ¬∑ what we might be missing ¬∑ cost if wrong]

### Your Choices ([T] taste decisions)
[each: title (phase) ‚Äî drafted as X per P<n>; Y is also viable: one-line downstream impact]

### Assumptions made ([A])
[each: assumption ‚Üí artifact it touches ‚Üí the fact that would confirm or kill it]

### Auto-decided: [M] (full log: docs/enterprise/autoplan/<date>-decisions.md)

### Team scorecard
[one line per team run: artifacts ¬∑ consultant verdict ¬∑ gates passed]

### Human to-do list (aggregated)
[the union of every artifact's human to-dos, grouped by team ‚Äî signatures, filings,
account connections, professional reviews]
```

Cognitive-load rules: 0 challenges or 0 taste decisions ‚Üí omit that section; 8+ taste
decisions ‚Üí group by phase and warn the ambiguity was unusually high.

Options: **A)** Approve as-is ‚Üí suggest the review PR (`docs: enterprise bootstrap
review package`, or the matched `--refresh` scope) and stop ‚Äî committing is the user's
call. **B)** Approve with overrides ‚Üí apply the named overrides as new dated artifact
revisions, re-present. **C)** Interrogate ‚Üí answer, re-present. **D)** Revise ‚Üí re-run
only the affected phases per the propagation matrix (max 3 cycles). **E)** Discard ‚Üí
point at the restore path and the dated artifacts; delete nothing yourself.

---

## Important Rules

- **Never abort to interactive mode.** The user chose the auto pipeline; surface taste
  decisions at the gate instead of redirecting mid-run.
- **Two gates only:** the Fact Intake and the Final Approval Gate (plus any risk-posture
  questions the user opted to take inline). Everything between is silent execution.
- **Facts are sacred** (P1). When in doubt between asking and assuming: during Phase 0
  ask; after Phase 0 assume, mark, and surface.
- **Full depth means full depth.** The loaded skills' persona passes, playbooks, and
  gate tables are the spec ‚Äî a summary where an artifact should be is a skip.
- **Sequential order, always.** Strategy feeds positioning feeds ICP feeds the model ‚Äî
  running ahead produces confident fiction.
- **Never commit, push, sign, send, file, or publish.** Artifacts land in the working
  tree; the review PR and every external action belong to humans.
